Students get brief overview about the newest scientific literature in bioorganic chemistry. Every seminar bases on a recently published scientific paper presented by a student. First, the presenter gives short wider overview about the problem. Then the experimental and theoretical part of the paper will be critically analyzed and conclusion about the weak and strong sides of the paper will be discussed. Seminars take place in English. This gives students experience to present scientific results and to perform scientific discussions in English.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Give first experience to students in critical reading of new scientific publications in bioorganic chemistry. Give students experience in presentation of scientific data and perform scientific discussions in English.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who passed the course successfully: - knows at least particularly newest scientific literature in bioorganic chemistry - has experience in presentation of scientific results in English - has experience of scientific discussions in English.
